article.headline: Southern Illinois 75, Western Kentucky 70
article.story: BOWLING GREEN, Ky. (AP) -- Tony Young scored 22 points, including six 3-pointers, to lead Southern Illinois to a 75-70 win against Western Kentucky on Saturday night. The Salukis (7-1) led by as many as 16 points late in the first half, but a late charge by the Hilltoppers (8-2) closed the gap to 33-27 at halftime. Eight points in a row by Courtney Lee opened the second half to help Western Kentucky inch closer, with Southern Illinois never gaining a lead bigger than 10 in the second half. Two free throws by Orlando Mendez-Valdez gave the Hilltoppers their first and only lead at 59-58 with four minutes left. Southern Illinois countered with a 6-0 run to retake the lead for good at 64-59. Western Kentucky pulled within two and three points of Southern Illinois in the final two minutes, but the Salukis sealed the win at the free throw line. Five Salukis finished in double-figures. Randal Falker and Wesley Clemmons finished the contest with 12 points each. Bryan Mullins dished out a game-high seven assists for Southern Illinois before fouling out. Lee finished with a game-high 23 points in 38 minutes for the Hilltoppers on 8-of-18 shooting, including 7-of-8 from the free throw line. Tyrone Brazelton capped the game with 12 points and two assists for Western Kentucky. The Salukis controlled the post throughout the game, outscoring the Hilltoppers 28-16 in points in the paint.
